RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAALA rated close to the early pace, bid approaching the three eighths pole and raced in the two and three paths on the far turn, took the nod into the lane, ran clear mid-stretch and drew off the final sixteenth. FAR MORE took over into the opening turn and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole and raced at the rail on the far turn, gave up the lead into the lane, dropped back toward mid-stretch and had to settle for second best. PRINCESS MARGARET had a slim early lead then stalked into the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and showed little further. TAPTAP saved ground well off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn near the rail. OUR BREW raced off the rail the first turn and showed little response. LOCKDOWN VANNA was detained in the gate and consequently declared a non-starter.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 11800. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBAY gave early chase toward the inside, angled to the four path approaching the top of the lane, drifted leaving the turn but dug in under steady handling and got up and cleared ELEANORS JACK in the final yards. The latter drew clear at the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, raced at the rail on the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling but was caught in the final yards. CHARITABLE WINDSOR pressured the pace to the head of the lane then flattened inside the eighth pole. JEFFERSON SECURITY gave chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. BEAR'S ESTATE gave chase outside and rounded the turn about the seven path. HE'S ON THE LINE gave chase through the backstretch and faded on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Eleanors Jack
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,rail turn,caught final yards

ENTRY.NAME: He's On the Line
ENTRY.OWNER: Sperling Nancie S and Racanelli Mark Joseph

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SARAH'S CANDY CAMP settled in the three path the first turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and improved in the four path on the far turn, was carried to the outside leaving the turn but dug in under steady handling and got up the final strides. LOVE IS WICKED veered in at the break then saved ground on the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage three wide on the far turn, drifted leaving the turn and dueled to a brief lead mid-stretch, but was caught in the final strides. MR. DUMBLEDORE settled off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced at the rail on the far turn, angled to the three path leaving the turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. YES MY PRINCE tapered in and stalked two deep, challenged CHRISTOPHER'SHEART leaving the three eighths pole, contested even terms two deep midway on the far turn but flattened stride leaving the eighth pole. The latter came away awkwardly and rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn and relented the final sixteenth. YACHTSMEN raced in the four path the first turn, left the turn outside and gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, but showed little response. RUDD'S ROCKET was never a factor. GOGO GADGET came away awkwardly then stalked from the three path the first turn, but faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Love Is Wicked
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered in break,saved ground,bid 3/8,3wd far turn,led 1/16,caught

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 12700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 2, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORT FORTITUDE rounded the first turn about the three path and was eased out entering the backstretch, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and dug in under steady handling to get up the final yards. FOX RED rated a slim lead off the rail, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and was met while between horses toward the quarter pole, dug in gamely leaving the far turn but was caught in the final yards. SHANGHAI WARRIOR stalked three wide, challenged toward the five sixteenths pole and contested even terms three wide on the far turn and remained a factor to mid-stretch before flattening stride. MAGICAL EXPRESS rated close inside, challenged nearing the five sixteenths pole and contested even terms at the rail on the far turn, but flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. SKILLFUL saved early ground while racing well back and never factored. MAKE THE WAY CLEAR showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Magical Express
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus Joy Kevin J and McMahon Michael H

ENTRY.NAME: Fort Fortitude
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,4p far turn,up final yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS BEE BOP took over while tapering in and rated the pace, was urged nearing the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn then vigorously handled in the lane. JLODIAMOND gave close chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail, eased out entering the stretch and settled for second. POUR ME A DRINK was bumped inward and into GHOSTLY ANNA leaving the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path and came along to take third inside the sixteenth pole. The latter was bumped leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, raced at the rail on the turn and flattened in the lane. SING ME TO SLEEP ducked inward and into Pour Me A Drink leaving the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path and flattened in the lane. MY LUCKY DEIA gave chase and rounded the turn about the five path. LITTLEBOURBONGIRL angled to the outside and raced well back. SPECIAL KAYLEE gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. SWIPE THAT CANDY gave chase and rounded the turn about the three path.

ENTRY.NAME: My Lucky Deia
ENTRY.OWNER: O'Sullivan Farms LLC and Steinmann Eric

ENTRY.NAME: Pour Me a Drink
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Bee Bop
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace,urged away near 1/4,rail turn,vigorous handling lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 16600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,25 0 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN GOOD TROUBLE chased inside through the backstretch, entered the turn off the rail, left the turn three wide and took the lead past the eighth pole, drew clear inside the sixteenth and widened through later yards. MY SISTER CLURRIE set a pressured pace through the opening quarter mile, was met and dueled at even terms toward the five sixteenths pole, took the nod past the quarter, gave up the lead leaving the furlong pole but cleared second past the sixteenth. SHUTUPN'KISSME dueled to even terms at the rail approaching the five sixteenths pole, contested even terms at the rail on the turn but flattened nearing mid-stretch. JUBA'S HOUSE chased through the backstretch, came through the turn about the five path, left the turn outside and could only improve her position. LOLA FLO gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. CHEROKEE CASTLE gave chase through the backstretch, raced in range in the four path on the turn then weakened. GOT YOUR NUMBER was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: In Good Trouble
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,3wd into lane,up past 1/8,clear 1/16,widened drving

ENTRY.NAME: Shutupn'kissme
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled to even terms near 5/16,rail turn,flattened mid-stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since Octo ber 2 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 2 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL MAHOGANY came out across the path of Bali's Shade on the chute then closed to the lead approaching the seven sixteenths pole and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the quarter, rounded the turn at the rail, dug in under steady stretch handling and just lasted. AMENDE CHARLIE chased inside through the backstretch, rounded the turn at the rail, dug in through the stretch and was gaining steadily on the winner. LION OF THE SEA was bumped, jostled then pinched back on the chute and settled into stride, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the turn, eased out approaching the head of the lane and finished strong while gaining on the top two. BALI'S SHADE exchanged contact with Lion Of The Sea then pinched back on the chute, picked up the chase leaving the chute and raced near the rail on the turn, had aim mid-stretch but flattened late yards. THE ILLUSIONIST pressured the pace and raced close off the rail on the turn, but flattened stride inside the eighth pole. MYGIDGETMARIE gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn and showed little in the lane. PURE NONSENSE exchanged contact with. DAN THE MAN CAN leaving the gate then gave chase through the backstretch, but faded off the rail on the turn. The latter broke through prior the start, exchanged contact with Pure Nonsense leaving the gate and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Mahogany
ENTRY.COMMENT: came out chute,up near 7/16,pressured 1/4,rail turn,just lasted

ENTRY.NAME: Lion of the Sea
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped,jostled break,pinched back,chase,rail turn,gaining top two

ENTRY.NAME: Dan the Man Can
ENTRY.OWNER: A and B Racing Stable LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CREOLE took the lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was given rein approaching the quarter pole, widened at the rail on the far turn and finished on her own initiative. PLANET FROLIC tapered in and stalked the early pace two deep, gave chase toward the five sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and had to settle for second best. SOMEBODY LOVES ME rounded the opening turn about the three path, left the turn outside and gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn then flattened in the lane. LILY THE KID saved ground on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. DASHING LASS was forced out leaving the gate and saved early ground. HERECOMESPUDD ducked out leaving the gate, raced in the four path on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. CHEYENNE SPRING rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded nearing the far turn. HEY MACARENA broke a step slow and saved ground on the first turn, showed little response and was eased from the five sixteenths pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Creole
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,given rein near 1/4,widened,own initiative lane
